prompt:
The file seed/chart.png contains a grouped bar chart showing quarterly revenue data for 5 companies across 4 quarters (Q1-Q4).

Your task is to extract the data from this chart image into structured JSON. You may use Python, PIL, or shell tools to analyze the image.

Write the extracted data to workspace/extracted.json in this format:
{
  "companies": [
    {
      "name": "<company name>",
      "q1": <revenue value>,
      "q2": <revenue value>,
      "q3": <revenue value>,
      "q4": <revenue value>
    },
    ...
  ]
}

Extract the company names from the chart legend and the revenue values from the bar heights. Values should be numeric (not strings).
